This is in a new conda env with no pre-existing ipython.

Something is definitely wrong, because `from IPython.external import pexpect` does not exist in IPython 4.0. That means you have some parts of IPython that are not from 4.0. Perhaps this is a problem with the conda package. Try reinstalling IPython:

```
conda uninstall ipython
conda install ipython
```

and see if it is resolved.

You may also want to check `ipython -V` to see what version IPython thinks it is.

I did some more testing. The following work fine:
- new environment with jupyter created from a new miniconda install.
- jupyter install in root of new miniconda install
- new environment with jupyter in a new anaconda install
- jupyter install in root of new anaconda install

Which implies that this is a problem with my local environment.

Problem fixed (for me at least).

I noticed that my ipython installs were coming from a cache rather than a new download. I 'fixed' the error by physically deleting all ipython packages from `anaconda/pkgs` and then reinstalling. There is probably a better way of fixing it (possibly with `conda clean`) but I can't test now because the bad environment is gone.

I've no idea how it went bad in the first place, but this is a fairly old anaconda install.

I suspect it's a conda packaging issue. I don't know the root cause - if an early build of a conda package was messed up, or if something got confused in the install process, but there shouldn't be anything for us to do here, and it seems to be fixed.

@asmeurer do you have any insight on what might cause a package to have contents from an earlier version?
A possibility is that if you `pip install IPython` and then `conda install ipython` a newer version over it it won't remove any files that should have been deleted.
@asmeurer good to know. I don't think that's exactly what happened here, because the error is happening in a file that is still around, but the content of the file has been modified.
Had exactly the same issue in deleting an environment and recreating another one with same name. I  solved the prob cleaning (conda clean -p -t -i -y) before creating the new enviro
